Female with unpaired pleopods 2-5 on left side or less frequently on right side, as follows: pleopods 2-4 biramous, well developed, and reduced biramous or uniramous and vestigial pleopod 5 (see 
"Variations"
). Brood pouch large, subquadrate, distal margin scalloped and fringed with setae.
